modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate COAP messages, handle request routing, and manage asynchronous connections using Lwt. Operates on byte sequences, message structures, and endpoint configurations. Used to implement lightweight IoT protocols in networked applications with non-blocking I/O.

Handles CoAP protocol communication using Lwt for asynchronous operations. Accepts incoming messages, processes them with a provided handler function, and sends responses. Designed for building lightweight, concurrent IoT servers that respond to CoAP requests over UDP.
